Shared decision making discussed. Referrals put in as requested, she did not want any meds I could send or any other orders or referrals. Reviewed supportive care. Reviewed preventative health care needs, pt declined anything further today, agrees to follow up.
Health promotion reviewed. Follow the guidelines at cdc.gov. Stay up to date on your vaccines. To sign up for the covid-19 vaccine through CCHS text the word Vaccine to 91999 or walk in for nurse visit for vaccine. Follow low sodium heart healthy plant based diet, healthy activity and healthy weight, we have counseling and nutritionist services if ever needed. 30 minutes of physical activity 5 times per week is recommended and can be customized to work with your past medical history. Increasing your steps or movement in the way that you can each day if possible is very beneficial and recommended. Try to eat mostly fruits, vegetables, nuts (if not allergic), beans, seeds, whole grains like quinoa, steel cut oatmeal, wild rice, barley, farro, and try to drink only water, 8 glasses a day. May drink low calorie electrolyte drinks if needed with sweating a lot with work out or outside in heat and sweating a lot. Avoid soda, juice and milk. Go to nutritionfacts.org or oldwayspt.org to find healthy recipes and information about vitamins and minerals. Follow the healthy shopping list given in clinic that says prescription for health. Reviewed supportive care at length. Make sure to have an annual physical every year. We have dental, pediatric and women's health services. Go to Christcommunityhealth.org for locations and phone numbers. Pt declined anything further today, agrees to follow up. Go to the ER with any emergency needs. Emergency signs and when to go to ER reviewed
Goal blood pressure less than 140/90 and ideally less than 130/80. Contact us with home readings.
Goal blood sugar less than 154, contact us with home readings.
More than 40 minutes spent reviewing chart and with history and exam and counseling with patient and with coordination of care.
